ng island the towns along long islands south shore experienced severe damage many homes were destroyed and many more were damaged due to extensive flooding the foundation partnered with newsday to target individuals and families in greatest need of disaster relief services the result is the following grants to a diverse set of qualified nonprofit agencies helping communities hardest hit on long island get back on their feet to recover and rebuild about the grants catholic charities diocese of rockville centre  for hurricane sandy case management services central council of the society of st vincent de paul in the diocese of rockville centre  for hurricane sandy direct aid long island family assistance relief community development corporation of long island inc  for relief for long island communities affected by superstorm sandy family service league inc  for long island storm urgent relief fund federation employment and guidance services  for the liftingup long island hurricane response initiative health and welfare council of long island inc  for long island superstorm sandy unmet needs roundtable hispanic brotherhood of rockville centre inc  for hurricane sandy disaster relief program island harvest ltd  for long island hurricane sandy disaster relief long island volunteer center  for long island disaster recovery center lutheran social services of new york  for new life center  long island program north shore child and family guidance center  for long island project hope program salvation army  for hurricane sandy recovery relief long island the united methodist committee of relief division of global ministries of the united methodist church  for long island disaster response the mccormick foundation has conducted many disaster relief campaigns including  hurricane katrina southern california wildfires and the  midwest flooding the foundation has a structure in place to ensure quick relief which is vital after disaster situations the mccormick foundations hurricane katrina relief effort in  raised more than  million in just four days which was matched at  percent by the foundation in total the foundation and its partners have raised more than  million from nearly  donors since  over  grants totaling more than  million have been awarded to disaster relief programs about the robert r mccormick foundation  robert r mccormick foundation is committed to fostering communities of educated informed and engaged citizens through philanthropic programs cantigny park and museums the foundation helps develop citizen leaders and works to make life better in our communities the foundation was established as a charitable trust in  upon the death of colonel robert r mccormick the longtime editor and publisher of the chicago tribune the mccormick foundation is one of the nations largest foundations with more than  billion in assets the mccormick foundation continues mccormicks legacy by partnering with media outlets such as newsday sports teams and philanthropic organizations across the country to encourage local giving inspire civic involvement and address human needs since  through newsday charities over  grants totaling more than  million have been awarded to nonprofit organizations on long island to learn more about the mccormick foundation visit wwwmccormickfoundationorg source robert r mccormick foundation related links httpwwwmccormickfoundationorg view table fullscreen view table fullscreen journalists and bloggers the news you need when you need it join pr newswire for journalists to access all of the free services designated to make your job easier in need of subject matter experts for your story submit a free profnet request and find the sources you need learn more mar    et preview new mccormick grants further strengthen youth civic education  engagement in illinois dec    et preview  new veterans in illinois younger poorer and in need of a new approach my news release contains wide tables view fullscreen read more may    et city